          <actionDate>2014-11-17</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Overseas Security Personnel Fairness Act - Amends the Defense Base Act with respect to payment of death benefits otherwise due a widow, widower, or surviving child of an individual employed at a military, air, or naval base outside of the United States who dies as a result of a war-risk hazard or act of terrorism occurring on or after September 11, 2001, when there is no person eligible for a death benefit under the Longshore and Harbor Workers' Compensation Act.</p> <p>Requires payment in such a case to:</p> <ul> <li> a beneficiary designated by the deceased, or</li> <li>the next of kin or the estate of the deceased under applicable state law if there is no designated beneficiary.</li> </ul> <p>Requires benefits to be paid from the Employees' Compensation Fund.</p>]]></text>
